               <msContents>
                  <summary>Late foliotation by curators, continuous.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <locus from="1v" to="3r">1v-3r</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <note/>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="4r" to="188v">4r-188v</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0002IHA">تنبيه الانام</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <note>19 l/p. Black ink and rubrications in red (chapters, "allahumma", Muhammad), red marks at the end of each prayer. Some final hā' of rubricated sections (faṣl) are written in a sophisticad way. F.186r, tatimmat al-kitāb, followed by a du'a for its author, copyist, reader, administrator (nāẓir), auditor (sāmi'), and audience (ḥāḍir), followed by 2 empty folios (186v, 187r), followed by a du'a and the colophon (187v-188v). In several places, the copyist had to deal with the left margin (Ff.111r and 113r, 123r, 124r, etc.). In the margin, each 100 prayers is indicated in red color; after 1.000, it is counted again by hundreeds. F.30v, indication in red in the margin. Few corrections in the margins (black ink) and in the text (f.111r, recent; 118v). Catchwords. Ff.82r-84r, around the text, one/two green-blue line frame. Dimension of 1 fol. is 35,2×23,1cm. F.24r, text repaired. Six first ff., f.188, repaired.</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
