                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1">-1</locus>
                           <q>Date: the 24 of ṭərr 1974 (Ethiopian Calendar) corresponds to the 1st of February 1982 (Gregorian Calendar), which is a Monday.

1st l.: « Ṭärra (= le nom du mois ṭərr) 24/74, ‘a m (for « ‘amätä məḥrət », « the year of compassion », referring to the Christian Ethiopian Calendar?).
2d line: « Qədami käməššeto 8 sä[‘at ?] », i.e. « Qədame käməššətu… », « Saturday, night time, 8 o'clock ».
3d line: unread.
4th line: « Natnale »?</q>
                           <note>4 lines of a text in Amharic, recent, written with a blue ball pen. The script is unhandsome.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#1">-1</locus>
                           <q>??</q>
                           <note>9 lines of an uncomplete text in Arabic</note>
                        </item>
                     </t:list>
